#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:69
msgid "Take note of the HWaddr, this the NIC's MAC address."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:72
msgid ""
"Now you can decide what you would like the NIC to be called, and set up your "
"/etc/mactab, here's mine as an example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:78
msgid ""
"# Begin /etc/mactab # This file relates MAC addresses to interface names.  # "
"We need this so that we can force the name we want # even if the kernel "
"finds the interfaces in the # wrong order."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:81
msgid "# eth0 under 2.4, eth1 under 2.6 beannet 00:60:97:52:9A:94"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:84
msgid "# eth1 under 2.4, eth0 under 2.6 sparenet 00:A0:C9:43:8F:77"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:86
msgid "# End /etc/mactab"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:89
msgid ""
"If you run nameif (without parameters) now you will probably get an error "
"message, since nameif must be run when the interfaces are down."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:92
msgid "$ nameif cannot change name of eth0 to beannet: Device or resource busy"
msgstr ""

