#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"LFS Bootscript Changes\n"
"======================\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:123
msgid ""
"As we've seen, nameif needs to be run early in the boot cycle, before the "
"network interfaces are brought up.  This means adding it to "
"/etc/rc.d/init.d/network."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:125
msgid "Edit the start of the file as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:128
msgid "#!/bin/bash # Begin $rc_base/init.d/network - Network Control Script"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:131
msgid ""
"# Based on ethnet script from LFS-3.1 and earlier.  # Rewritten by Gerard "
"Beekmans - gerard@linuxfromscratch.org"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:135
msgid "source /etc/sysconfig/rc source $rc_functions source /etc/sysconfig/network"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:146
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"case \"$1\" in\n"
"    start)\n"
"         if [ -e /etc/mactab ]\n"
"         then\n"
"         # if /etc/mactab exists then set up the named interfaces\n"
"             nameif\n"
"         fi\n"
"         for file in $(grep -il \"ONBOOT=yes\" "
"$network_devices/ifconfig.*)\n"
"         do\n"
"......\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:148
msgid "This ensures that nameif is run with /etc/mactab, if that file exists."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:151
msgid ""
"Now go to /etc/sysconfig and change the name(s) of the interface(s) wherever "
"it(they) occur(s).  I made the following changes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1) '
#: origin/nameif.txt:155
msgid "edit /etc/sysconfig/network to specify the renamed GATEWAY_IF."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2) '
#: origin/nameif.txt:155
msgid ""
"rename /etc/network-devices/ifconfig.eth0 to ifconfig.yourname and edit it "
"so that DEVICE=yourname."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/nameif.txt:159
msgid ""
"If you use the Beyond Linux From Scratch instructions to use DHCP, then you "
"will need to substitute your new NIC names in the scripts and filenames in "
"the appropriate places."
msgstr ""

